<p>
“Body Parts”-recommend this phrase be added to important terms list as it occurs in Matthew, Romans and James.  
</p>

<p>
The UDB translaton is good, except recommend that it be changed from:
It is opposed to what with my MIND I desire to do, and it makes me do what my old sinful HEART wants me to do
to:
It is opposed to what with my HEART I desire to do, and it makes me do what my old sinful MIND wants me to do.
</p>

<p>
Scripture teaches that God has gives us a new heart when we are saved,but that we must renew our minds. See Romans 2:29, 6:17, 2 Corinthians 3:3, Ephesians 3:17, Jeremiah 24:7 etc.  Our heart is what is changed in the new birth.  
</p>
